    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractPersistenceRenderer

        public AbstractPersistenceRenderer(KeyValueBuilder builder,
                           java.util.Map<java.lang.Class<?>,Decorator> decorators)
        Abstract class that holds the information about the KeyValueBuilder and the Decorators.
        Parameters:
        builder - The KeyValueBuilder used to flatten out the semantic model into a list of key-value pairs. This builder will call the PersistenceRenderer.buildKeyValuePair(org.freezedry.persistence.tree.InfoNode, String, java.util.List, boolean) method of the classes implementing this class as part of a recursive algorithm to flatten the semantic model.
        decorators - The mapping between the classes and their decorators. The decorators format the strings, ints, doubles, etc. For example, by default, strings are surrounded by quotes.

      • AbstractPersistenceRenderer

        public AbstractPersistenceRenderer(KeyValueBuilder builder)
        Constructor for the PersistenceRenderers that stores the associated. Uses the default mapping for classes and their decorators. PersistenceWriter needed for recursion.
        Parameters:
        builder - The associated PersistenceWriter

      • addDecorator

        public Decorator addDecorator(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                     Decorator decorator)
        Adds a new Decorator for the specified class. If the specified class already had a Decorator, then overwrites that association and returns the previous Decorator. Recall that Decorators format keys and values. For example, by default, Strings are surrounded with quotes.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The class to associate with the specified Decorator
        decorator - The Decorator to associated with the class.
        Returns:
        the Decorator previously associated with the specified Class.

      • getDecorator

        public Decorator getDecorator(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Finds the Decorator associated with the class. If the specified class doesn't have a decorator, then it searches for the closest parent class (inheritance) and returns that. In this case, it adds an entry to the decorator map for the specified class associating it with the returned decorator (performance speed-up for subsequent calls).
        Parameters:
        clazz - The class for which to find a decorator
        Returns:
        the Decorator associated with the class

      • getDecorator

        public Decorator getDecorator(java.lang.String value)
        Returns the Decorator that was used to decorate the specified value, or if no such Decorator was found, returns null.
        Parameters:
        value - The decorated value (must be either a integer, double, string)
        Returns:
        the Decorator that was used to decorate the specified value, or if no such Decorator was found, returns null.

      • containsDecorator

        public boolean containsDecorator(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        Finds the PersistenceRenderer associated with the class. If the specified class doesn't have a renderer, then it searches for the closest parent class (inheritance) and returns that. In this case, it adds an entry to the persistence renderer map for the specified class associating it with the returned persistence renderer (performance speed-up for subsequent calls).
        Parameters:
        clazz - The class for which to find a persistence renderer
        Returns:
        the true if a persistence renderer was found; false otherwise
